message.content:
1. The intervention led to an increase in the mean scores of total PA four months after it was implemented.
2. The p-value for the increase in total PA was less than 0.001.
3. The effect size (ES) for the increase in total PA was 4.77.
4. The intervention led to an increase in the mean scores of physical fitness tests including flexibility.
5. The p-value for the increase in flexibility was less than 0.001.
6. The effect size (ES) for the increase in flexibility was 1.59.
7. The intervention led to an increase in the mean scores of muscular endurance.
8. The p-value for the increase in muscular endurance was less than 0.001.
9. The effect size (ES) for the increase in muscular endurance was 2.0.
10. The intervention led to an increase in the mean scores of cardiorespiratory endurance.
11. The p-value for the increase in cardiorespiratory endurance was less than 0.001.
12. The effect size (ES) for the increase in cardiorespiratory endurance was 0.51.
13. The intervention led to a decrease in the mean scores of the agility test.
14. The p-value for the decrease in agility test scores was less than 0.001.
15. The effect size (ES) for the decrease in agility test scores was -0.51.
16. The intervention led to a decrease in the mean scores of sedentary behavior.
17. The p-value for the decrease in sedentary behavior was less than 0.01.
18. The effect size (ES) for the decrease in sedentary behavior was -0.74.
19. The changes in scores were observed in the intervention group compared to the control group.

messages.content:
Statement: Four months after the intervention, an increase in the mean scores of total PA (p<0.001, ES=4.77), physical fitness tests including flexibility (p<0.001, ES=1.59), muscular endurance (p<0.001, ES=2.0), cardiorespiratory endurance (p<0.001, ES=0.51), and a decrease in mean scores of agility test (p<0.001, ES= − 0.51) and sedentary behavior (p<0.01, ES=− 0.74) was observed in the intervention group compared to the control group.
